quran[190]{c,v,t}:
  21,1,"Their reckoning draws nigh to men, yet in heedlessness they turn aside"
  21,2,"No reminder comes to them from their Lord of late, but they listen while they mock"
  21,3,"and their hearts make sport thereof! And those who do wrong discourse secretly (saying), 'Is this man aught but a mortal like yourselves? will ye accede to magic, while ye can see"
  21,4,"Say, 'My Lord knows what is said in the heavens and the earth, He hears and knows"
  21,5,"Nay!' they say, 'a jumble of dreams; nay! he has forged it; nay! he is a poet; but let him bring us a sign as those of yore were sent"
  21,6,No city before them which we destroyed believed - how will they believe
  21,7,Nor did we send before them any but men whom we inspired? Ask ye the people of the Scriptures if ye do not know
  21,8,"Nor did we make them bodies not to eat food, nor were they immortal"
  21,9,"Yet we made our promise to them good, and we saved them and whom we pleased; but we destroyed those who committed excesses"
  21,10,We have sent down to you a book in which is a reminder for you; have ye then no sense
  21,11,"How many a city which had done wrong have we broken up, and raised up after it another people"
  21,12,And when they perceived our violence they ran away from it
  21,13,"Run not away, but return to what ye delighted in, and to your dwellings! haply ye will be questioned"
  21,14,"Said they, 'O woe is us! verily, we were wrong-doers"
  21,15,"And that ceased not to be their cry until we made them mown down,- smouldering out"
  21,16,We did not create the heaven and the earth and what is between the two in play
  21,17,"Had we wished to take to a sport, we would have taken to one from before ourselves; had we been bent on doing so"
  21,18,"Nay, we hurl the truth against falsehood and it crashes into it, and lo! it vanishes, but woe to you for what ye attribute (to God)"
  21,19,"His are whosoever are in the heavens and the earth, and those who are with Him are not too big with pride for His service, nor do they weary"
  21,20,They celebrate His praises by night and day without intermission
  21,21,Or have they taken gods from the earth who can raise up (the dead)
  21,22,"Were there in both (heaven and earth) gods beside God, both would surely have been corrupted. Celebrated then be the praise of God, the Lord of the throne, above what they ascribe"
  21,23,"He shall not be questioned concerning what He does, but they shall be questioned"
  21,24,"Have they taken gods beside Him? Say, 'Bring your proofs. This is the reminder of those who are with me, and of those who were before me.' Nay, most of them know not the truth, and they do turn aside"
  21,25,"We have not sent any prophet before thee, but we inspired him that, 'There is no god but Me, so serve ye Me"
  21,26,"And they say, 'The Merciful has taken a son; celebrated be His praise!' - Nay, honoured servants"
  21,27,they do not speak until He speaks; but at His bidding do they act
  21,28,"He knows what is before them, and what is behind them, and they shall not intercede except for him whom He is pleased with; and they shrink through fear"
  21,29,"And whoso of them should say, 'Verily, I am god instead of Him,' such a one we recompense with hell; thus do we recompense the wrongdoers"
  21,30,"Do not those who misbelieve see that the heavens and the earth were both solid, and we burst them asunder; and we made from water every living thing - will they then not believe"
  21,31,"And we placed on the earth firm mountains lest it should move with them, and He made therein open roads for paths, haply they may be guided"
  21,32,and we made the heaven a guarded roof; yet from our signs they turn aside
  21,33,"He it is who created the night and the day, and the sun and the moon, each floating in a sky"
  21,34,"We never made for any mortal before thee immortality; what, if thou shouldst die, will they live on for aye"
  21,35,"Every soul shall taste of death! we will test them with evil and with good, as a trial; and unto us shall they return"
  21,36,"And when those who misbelieve see thee, they only take thee for a jest, 'Is this he who mentions your gods?' Yet they at the mention of the Merciful do disbelieve"
  21,37,"Man is created out of haste. I will show, you my signs; but do not hurry Me"
  21,38,"And they say, 'When will this threat (come to pass), if ye tell the truth"
  21,39,"Did those who misbelieve but know when the fire shall not be warded off from their faces nor from their backs, and they shall not be helped"
  21,40,"Nay, it shall come on them suddenly, and shall dumbfounder them, and they shall not be able to repel it, nor shall they be respited"
  21,41,"Prophets before thee have been mocked at, but that whereat they jested encompassed those who mocked"
  21,42,"Say, 'Who shall guard you by night and by day from the Merciful?' Nay, but they from the mention of their Lord do turn aside"
  21,43,"Have they gods to defend them against us? These cannot help themselves, nor shall they be abetted against us"
  21,44,"Nay, but we have granted enjoyment to these men and to their fathers whilst life was prolonged. Do they not see that we come to the land and shorten its borders? Shall they then prevail"
  21,45,"Say, 'I only warn you by inspiration;' but the deaf hear not the call when they are warned"
  21,46,"But if a blast of the torment of thy Lord touches them, they will surely say, 'O, woe is us! verily, we were wrong-doers"
  21,47,"We will place just balances upon the resurrection day, and no soul shall be wronged at all, even though it be the weight of a grain of mustard seed, we will bring it; for we are good enough at reckoning up"
  21,48,"We did give to Moses and Aaron the Discrimination, and a light and a reminder to those who fear"
  21,49,who are afraid of their Lord in secret; and who at the Hour do shrink
  21,50,"This is a blessed reminder which we have sent down, will ye then deny it"
  21,51,And we gave Abraham a right direction before; for about him we knew
  21,52,"When he said to his father and to his people, 'What are these images to which ye pay devotion"
  21,53,"Said they, 'We found our fathers serving them"
  21,54,"Said he, 'Both you and your fathers have been in obvious error"
  21,55,"They said, 'Dost thou come to us with the truth, or art thou but of those who play"
  21,56,"He said, 'Nay, but your Lord is Lord of the heavens and the earth, which He originated; and I am of those who testify to this"
  21,57,"and, by God! I will plot against your idols after ye have turned and shown me your backs"
  21,58,"So he brake them all in pieces, except a large one they had; that haply they might refer it to that"
  21,59,"Said they, 'Who has done this with our gods? verily, he is of the wrong-doers"
  21,60,"They said, 'We heard a youth mention them who is called Abraham"
  21,61,"Said they, 'Then bring him before the eyes of men; haply they will bear witness"
  21,62,"Said they, 'Was it thou who did this to our gods, O Abraham"
  21,63,"Said he, 'Nay, it was this largest of them; but ask them, if they can speak"
  21,64,"Then they came to themselves and said, 'Verily, ye are the wrong-doers"
  21,65,"Then they turned upside down again: 'Thou knewest that these cannot speak"
  21,66,"Said he, 'Will ye then serve, beside God, what cannot profit you at all, nor harm you"
  21,67,"fie upon you, and what ye serve beside God! have ye then no sense"
  21,68,"Said they, 'Burn him, and help your gods, if ye are going to do so"
  21,69,"We said, 'O fire! be thou cool and a safety for Abraham"
  21,70,"They desired to plot against him, but we made them the losers"
  21,71,And we brought him and Lot safely to the land which we have blessed for the world
  21,72,"and we bestowed upon him Isaac and Jacob as a fresh gift, and each of them we made righteous persons"
  21,73,"and we made them high priests to guide (men) by our bidding, and we inspired them to do good works, and to be steadfast in prayer, and to give alms; and they did serve us"
  21,74,"And Lot, to him we gave judgment and knowledge, and we brought him safely out of the city which had done vile acts; verily, they were a people who wrought abominations"
  21,75,"And we made him enter into our mercy; verily, he was of the righteous"
  21,76,"And Noah, when he cried aforetime, and we answered him and saved him and his people from the mighty trouble"
  21,77,"and we helped him against the people who said our signs were lies; verily, they were a bad people, so we drowned them all together"
  21,78,"And David and Solomon, when they gave judgment concerning the field, when some people's sheep had strayed therein at night; and we testified to their judgment"
  21,79,"and this we gave Solomon to understand. To each of them we gave judgment and knowledge; and to David we subjected the mountains to celebrate our praises, and the birds too,- it was we who did it"
  21,80,"And we taught him the art of making coats of mail for you, to shield you from each other's violence; are ye then grateful"
  21,81,"And to Solomon (we subjected) the wind blowing stormily, to run on at his bidding to the land which Ave have blessed, - for all things did we know"
  21,82,"and some devils to dive for him, and to do other works beside that; and we kept guard over them"
  21,83,"And Job, when he cried to his Lord, 'As for me, harm has touched me, but Thou art the most merciful of the merciful ones"
  21,84,"And we answered him, and removed from him the distress that was upon him; and we gave his family, and the like of them with them, as a mercy from us, and a remembrance to those who serve us"
  21,85,"And Ishmael, and Idris, and Dhu 'l Kifl, all of these were of the patient"
  21,86,"and we made them enter into our mercy; verily, they were among the righteous"
  21,87,"And Dhu 'nnun, when he went away in wrath and thought that we had no power over him; and he cried out in the darkness, ' There is no god but Thou, celebrated be Thy praise! Verily, I was of the evildoers"
  21,88,"And we answered him, and saved him from the trouble. Thus do we save believers"
  21,89,"And Zachariah, when he cried unto his Lord, 'O Lord! leave me not alone; for thou art the best of heirs"
  21,90,"And we answered him, and bestowed upon him John; and we made his wife right for him; verily, these vied in good works, and called on us with longing and dread, and were humble before us"
  21,91,"And she who guarded her private parts, and we breathed into her of our Spirit, and we made her and her son a sign unto the worlds"
  21,92,"Verily, this your nation is one nation; and I am your Lord, so serve me"
  21,93,But they cut up their affair amongst themselves; they all shall return to us
  21,94,"and he who acts aright, and he who is a believer, there is no denial of his efforts, for, verily, we will write them down for him"
  21,95,There is a ban upon a city which we have destroyed that they shall not return
  21,96,"until Yagug and Magug are let out, and they from every hummock shall glide forth"
  21,97,"And the true promise draws nigh, and lo! they are staring - the eyes of those who misbelieve! O, woe is us! we were heedless of this, nay, we were wrong-doers"
  21,98,"Verily, ye, and what ye serve beside God, shall be the pebbles of hell, to it shall ye go down"
  21,99,"Had these been God's they would not have gone down thereto: but all shall dwell therein for aye"
  21,100,"for them therein is groaning, but they therein shall not be heard"
  21,101,"Verily, those for whom the good (reward) from us was fore-ordained, they from it shall be kept far away"
  21,102,"they shall not hear the slightest sound thereof, and they in what their souls desire shall dwell for aye"
  21,103,"The greatest terror shall not grieve them; and the angels shall meet them, (saying), 'This is your day which ye were promised"
  21,104,"The day when we will roll up the heavens as es-Sigill rolls up the books; as we produced it at its first creation will we bring it back again - a promise binding upon us; verily, we are going to do it"
  21,105,And already have we written in the Psalms after the reminder that the earth shall my righteous servants inherit
  21,106,"Verily, in this is preaching for a people who serve me"
  21,107,We have only sent thee as a mercy to the worlds
  21,108,"Say, 'I am only inspired that your God is one God; are ye then resigned"
  21,109,"But if they turn their backs say, 'I have proclaimed (war) against all alike, but I know not if what ye are threatened with be near or far"
  21,110,"Verily, He knows what is spoken openly, and He knows what ye hide"
  21,111,"I know not, haply, it is a trial for you and a provision for a season"
  21,112,"Say, 'My Lord! judge thou with truth! and our Lord is the Merciful whom we ask for aid against what they ascribe"
  22,1,"O ye folk! fear your Lord. Verily, the earthquake of the Hour is a mighty thing"
  22,2,"On the day ye shall see it, every suckling woman shall be seared away from that to which she gave suck; and every pregnant woman shall lay down her load; and thou shalt see men drunken, though they be not drunken: but the torment of God is severe"
  22,3,"And amongst men is one who wrangles about God without knowledge, and follows every rebellious devil"
  22,4,"against whom it is written down that whoso takes him for a patron, verily, he will lead him astray, and will guide him towards the torment of the blaze"
  22,5,"O ye folk! if ye are in doubt about the raising (of the dead),- verily, we created you from earth, then from a clot, then from congealed blood, then from a morsel, shaped or shapeless, that we may explain to you. And we make what we please rest in the womb until an appointed time; then we bring you forth babes; then let you reach your full age; and of you are some who die; and of you are some who are kept back till the most decrepit age, till he knows no longer aught of knowledge. And ye see the earth parched, and when we send down water on it, it stirs and swells, and brings forth herbs of every beauteous kind"
  22,6,"That is because God, He is the truth, and because He quickens the dead, and because He is mighty over all"
  22,7,"and because the Hour is coming, there is no doubt therein, and because God raises up those who are in the tombs"
  22,8,And amongst men is one who wrangles about God without knowledge or guidance or an illuminating book
  22,9,"twisting his neck from the way of God; for him is disgrace in this world, and we will make him taste, upon the resurrection day, the torment of burning"
  22,10,"That is for what thy hands have done before, and for that God is not unjust unto His servants"
  22,11,"And amongst men is one who serves God (wavering) on a brink; and if there befall him good, he is comforted; but if there befall him a trial, he turns round again, and loses this world and the next - that is an obvious loss"
  22,12,"He calls, besides God, on what can neither harm him nor profit him;- that is a wide error"
  22,13,"He calls on him whose harm is nigher than his profit,- a bad lord and a bad comrade"
  22,14,"Verily, God makes those who believe and do aright enter into gardens beneath which rivers flow; verily, God does what He will"
  22,15,He who thinks that God will never help him in this world or the next - let him stretch a cord to the roof and put an end to himself; and let him cut it and see if his stratagem will remove what he is enraged at
  22,16,"Thus have we sent down manifest signs; for, verily, God guides whom He will"
  22,17,"Verily, those who believe, and those who are Jews, and the Sabaeans, and the Christians, and the Magians, and those who join other gods with God, verily, God will decide between them on the resurrection day; verily, God is witness over all"
  22,18,"Do they not see that God, whosoever is in the heavens adores Him, and whosoever is in the earth, and the sun, and the moon, and the stars, and the mountains, and the beasts, and many among men, though many a one deserves the torments? Whomsoever God abases there is none to honour him; verily, God does what He pleases"
  22,19,"These are two disputants who dispute about their Lord, but those who misbelieve, for them are cut out garments of fire, there shall be poured over their heads boiling water"
  22,20,wherewith what is in their bellies shall be dissolved and their skins too
  22,21,and for them are maces of iron
  22,22,"Whenever they desire to come forth therefrom through pain, they are sent back into it:. 'And taste ye the torment of the burning"
  22,23,"Verily, God will make those who believe and do right enter into gardens beneath which rivers flow; they shall be bedecked therein with bracelets of gold and with pearls, and their garments therein shall be of silk"
  22,24,"and they shall be guided to the goodly speech, and they shall be guided to the laudable way"
  22,25,"Verily, those who misbelieve and who turn men away from God's path and the Sacred Mosque, which we have made for all men alike, the dweller therein, and the stranger, and he who desires therein profanation with injustice, we will make him taste grievous woe"
  22,26,"And when we established for Abraham the place of the House, (saying), 'Associate naught with me, but cleanse my House for those who make the circuits, for those who stand to pray, for those who bow, and for those too who adore"
  22,27,"And proclaim amongst men the Pilgrimage; let them come to you on foot and on every slim camel, from every deep pass"
  22,28,"that they may witness advantages for them, and may mention the name of God for the stated days over what God has provided them with of brute beasts, then eat thereof and feed the badly off, the poor"
  22,29,"Then let them finish the neglect of their persons, and let them pay their vows and make the circuit round the old House"
  22,30,"That do. And whoso magnifies the sacred things of God it is better for him with his Lord. 'Cattle are lawful for you, except what is recited to you; and avoid the abomination of idols, and avoid speaking falsely"
  22,31,"being 'Hanifs to God, not associating aught with Him; for he who associates aught with God, it is as though he had fallen from heaven, and the birds snatch him up, or the wind blows him away into a far distant place"
  22,32,"That - and he who makes grand the symbols of God, they come from piety of heart"
  22,33,"Therein have ye advantages for an appointed time, then the place for sacrificing them is at the old House"
  22,34,"To every nation have we appointed rites, to mention the name of God over what He has provided them with of brute beasts; and your God is one God, to Him then be resigned, and give glad tidings to the lowly"
  22,35,"whose hearts when God is mentioned are afraid, and to those who are patient of what befalls them, and to those who are steadfast in prayer and of what we have given them expend in alms"
  22,36,"The bulky (camels) we have made for you one of the symbols of God, therein have ye good; so mention the name of God over them as they stand in a row, and when they fall down (dead) eat of them, and feed the easily contented and him who begs"
  22,37,"Thus have we subjected them to you; haply, ye may give thanks! Their meat will never reach to God, nor yet their blood, but the piety from you will reach to Him. Thus hath He subjected them to you that ye may magnify God for guiding you: and give thou glad tidiness to those who do good"
  22,38,"Verily, God will defend those who believe; verily, God loves not any misbelieving traitor"
  22,39,"Permission is given to those who fight because they have been wronged, - and, verily, God to help them has the might"
  22,40,"who have been driven forth from their homes undeservedly, only for that they said, 'Our Lord is God;' and were it not for God's repelling some men with others, cloisters and churches and synagogues and mosques, wherein God's name is mentioned much, would be destroyed. But God will surely help him who helps Him; verily, God is powerful, mighty"
  22,41,"Who, if we establish them in the earth, are steadfast in prayer, and give alms, and bid what is right, and forbid what is wrong; and God's is the future of affairs"
  22,42,"But if they call thee liar, the people of Noah called him liar before them, as did 'Ad and Thamud"
  22,43,"and the people of Abraham, and the people of Lot"
  22,44,"and the fellows of Midian; and Moses was called a liar too: but I let the misbelievers range at large, and then I seized on them, and how great was the change"
  22,45,"And how many a city have we destroyed while it yet did wrong, and it was turned over on its roofs, and (how many) a deserted well and lofty palace"
  22,46,"Have they not travelled on through the land? and have they not hearts to understand with, or ears to hear with? for it is not their eyes which are blind, but blind are the hearts which are within their breasts"
  22,47,"They will bid thee hasten on the torment, but God will never fail in his promise; for, verily, a day with thy Lord is as a thousand years of what ye number"
  22,48,"And to how many a city have I given full range while it yet did wrong! then I seized on it, and unto me was the return"
  22,49,"Say, 'O ye folk! I am naught but a plain warner to you"
  22,50,"but those who believe and do right, for them is forgiveness and a generous provision"
  22,51,"but those who strive to discredit our signs, they are the fellows of hell"
  22,52,"We have not sent before thee any apostle or prophet, but that when he wished, Satan threw not something into his wish; but God annuls what Satan throws; then does God confirm his signs, and God is knowing, wise"
  22,53,"to make what Satan throws a trial unto those in whose hearts is sickness, and those whose hearts are hard; and, verily, the wrong - doers are in a wide schism"
  22,54,"and that those who have been given 'the knowledge' may know that it is the truth from thy Lord, and may believe therein, and that their hearts may be lowly; for, verily, God surely will guide those who believe into a right way"
  22,55,"But those who misbelieve will not cease to be in doubt thereof until the Hour comes on them suddenly, or there comes on them the torment of the barren day"
  22,56,"The kingdom on that day shall be God's, He shall judge between them; and those who believe and do aright shall be in gardens of pleasure"
  22,57,"but those who misbelieve and say our signs are lies, these - for them is shameful woe"
  22,58,"And those who flee in God's way, and then are slain or die, God will provide them with a goodly provision; for, verily, God is the best of providers"
  22,59,"He shall surely make them enter by an entrance that they like; for, verily, God is knowing, clement"
  22,60,"That (is so). Whoever punishes with the like of what he has been injured with, and shall then be outraged again, God shall surely help him; verily, God pardons, forgives"
  22,61,"That for that God joins on the night to the day, and joins on the day to the night, and that God is hearing, seeing"
  22,62,"that is for that God is the truth, and for that what ye call on beside Him is falsehood, and that God is the high, the great"
  22,63,"Hast thou not seen that God sends down from the sky water, and on the morrow the earth is green? verily, God is kind and well aware"
  22,64,"His is what is in the heavens and what is in the earth; and, verily, God is rich and to be praised"
  22,65,"Hast thou not seen that God has subjected for you what is in the earth, and the ship that runs on in the sea at His bidding, and He holds back the sky from falling on the earth save at His bidding? verily, God to men is gracious, merciful"
  22,66,"He it is who quickens you, then makes you die, then will He quicken you again - verily, man is indeed ungrateful"
  22,67,"For every nation have we made rites which they observe; let them not then dispute about the matter, but call upon thy Lord; verily, thou art surely in a right guidance"
  22,68,"But if they wrangle with thee, say, 'God best knows what ye do"
  22,69,God shall judge between them on the resurrection day concerning that whereon they disagreed
  22,70,"Didst thou not know that God knows what is in the heavens and the earth? verily, that is in a book; verily, that for God is easy"
  22,71,"And they serve beside God what He has sent down no power for, and what they have no knowledge of; but the wrong-doers shall have none to help them"
  22,72,"When our signs are read to them manifest, thou mayest recognise in the faces of those who misbelieve disdain; they well-nigh rush at those who recite to them our signs. Say, 'Shall I inform you of something worse than that for you, the Fire which God has promised to those who misbelieve? an evil journey shall it be"
  22,73,"O ye folk! a parable is struck out for you, so listen to it. Verily, those on whom ye call beside God could never create a fly if they all united together to do it, and if the fly should despoil them of aught they could not snatch it away from it - weak is both the seeker and the sought"
  22,74,"They do not value God at His true value; verily, God is powerful, mighty"
  22,75,"God chooses apostles of the angels and of men; verily, God hears and sees"
  22,76,He knows what is before them and what is behind them; and unto God affairs return
  22,77,"O ye who believe! bow down and adore, and serve your Lord, and do well, haply ye may prosper"
  22,78,"and fight strenuously for God, as is His due. He has elected you, and has not put upon you any hindrance by your religion,- the faith of your father Abraham. He has named you Muslims before and in this (book), that the Apostle may be a witness against you, and that ye may be witnesses against men. Be ye then steadfast in prayer, and give alms, and hold fast by God; He is your sovereign, and an excellent sovereign, and an excellent help"